source_objects.description: Become a database expert with these courses ranging from basic SQL to Hadoop and Oracle mastery.
source_objects.title: Database Design & Development

items.title: IBM Datastage For Administrators and Developers
items.headline: Zero to Hero in IBM Datastage with Datastage VM
objectives_summary: Students will learn to Create Parallel & Sequencer Datastage Jobs to implement Business Intelligence on any given requirement. Additionally, the course explains the different IBM Datastage Admin Activities with the concepts of Architecture, Partitioning & Deployment strategies. In Short, Zero to Hero in IBM Datastage.

items.title: Creating Reports with SQL Server 2012 Reporting Services
items.headline: A concise, fast-paced tutorial that demonstrates how to efficiently create a variety of practical reports with SSRS
objectives_summary: Utilize the Report Wizard to quickly get a report started
Format data in tables and matrices
Add interactive sorting and high-impact visualizations such as pie charts, gauges, and bar graphs

items.title: Data Warehousing for beginners.
items.headline: Learn to implement a Data Warehouse Solution from scratch
objectives_summary: Deploy and Configure SSIS packages.
Design and implement a data warehouse
Implement Data Flow in an SSIS Package

items.title: NoSQL Databases For Beginners
items.headline: Learn to Store and Retrieve Data  from a Database without using SQL
objectives_summary: Define views
Reduce data via reduce function
Deploy applications

items.title: Oracle Real Application Cluster
items.headline: Learn all the secrets to set a 2 nodes Oracle RAC with your virtual machine. The perfect simulaton for training !
objectives_summary: Install and set from scratch a 2 node cluster with Oracle 12c technology
Know all the important point to set a cluster with Oracle
Install and set  Oracle virtual box for RAC

items.title: SQL Server Administration (Mock Internship Program Part1)
items.headline: Ge the 'experience' you desperately need for a SQL Server Administration job by taking this course.
objectives_summary: At this end of the course, the student will have the necessary ‘experience’ in managing, configuring, installing, deploying, and creating a SQL Server environment to enhance the knowledge gained by the 7 courses.

items.title: Learn to Build SQL Query| Ultimate SQL and DataBase Concepts
items.headline: Learn SQL and Database Core Concepts: This SQL Tutorial will cover all Major SQL concepts to write Query from Scratch.
objectives_summary: SQL Fundamentals
Understand Complex SQL Concepts in Easy way using daily life examples
Construct SQL Statements

items.title: The Complete SQL Course 2021 - Learn by Doing - SQL Server
items.headline: Master SQL to an expert level with this SQL bootcamp - Use Advanced Queries for Data Analysis and Analytics - SQL Server
objectives_summary: How to write accurate SQL queries against a database
Use SQL to perform data analysis
Learn to perform GROUP BY Statements

items.title: MySQL Database MasterClass: Go From Pupil To Master!

visible_instructors.title: Rico Rodriguez
visible_instructors.name: Rico
visible_instructors.job_title: SQL Architect, Senior Software Developer, Project Manager

items.headline: This is a MySQL MasterClass that gets you immediate hands on experience with a database. From design to Master Class!
objectives_summary: Design a Complex Database For Any Line Of Business Application
Be Able To Write Complex SQL Statements
Be able to manipulate a massive amount of data in milliseconds.

items.title: The Comprehensive SQL Course 2021
items.headline: A bootcamp designed to help you master SQL and work with databases like Oracle, MySQL and Microsoft SQL Server
objectives_summary: Become proficient in SQL
Students will be able to apply SQL to real world problems
Boost your CV with one of the most in-demand skills in the data analysis and software development professions

items.title: Database Design for Relational Databases using SQL Server
items.headline: Learn Database Design Fundamentals and sharpen your SQL in under 5 hours. SQL Database Design explained for Beginners
objectives_summary: Learn Best Practices for Relational Database Design
Understand Relational Theory
Learn the data normalization process

items.title: Filemaker Time Registration for Freelancers
items.headline: A complete beginners course to learn the basics of Filemaker and some cool extra tricks while creating a real solution.
objectives_summary: Build their own Filemaker solution to manage time spent on various job for various clients.
Create basic filemaker tables, fields and relationships.
Make beautiful and practical Filemaker layouts and add all kinds of fun features.

items.title: Practice with Oracle RMAN
items.headline: This is a practice course. Here you'll find a lot of interesting demos and how to. Just to learn all the facets of RMAN
objectives_summary: Set rman catalog
Make all type of database backups
Understand concepts as compression and retention policy

items.title: SQL and Transact-SQL  (T-SQL)  For Beginners
items.headline: Learn SQL and T-SQL From Scratch and execute queries on SQL Server
objectives_summary: How to install SQL Server Database Management System
How to install SQL Server Management Studio -SSMS
How to create a database

items.title: Become an Oracle Database Administrator (DBA)
items.headline: Learn the essential tools you will need to function effectively as an Oracle DBA
objectives_summary: Start and Shut down a database
Backup and Recover Data
Create database objects like database,schema and tables

items.title: SQL SERVER Procedures&Concepts - Raise Above Beginner Level
items.headline: Build Stored Procedures, Dynamic Queries, Clauses, Pivot Operator, XML parsing, building Database templates and others
objectives_summary: Understand the concept of a Stored Procedure in a practical manner and embed inside of it other concepts like:
Cursors, Dynamic Queries, Pivots, XML Parsing, Clauses and others
Gain programming creativity
